Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.38,0:00:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know there's an awesome\Ntreasure at the end of this sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.61,0:00:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever gets it can be King\Nof the Pirates! Isn't that exciting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unheard-of adventures are waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.39,0:00:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage! Let that shred of courage grow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The horizons everyone\Ndreamed of were separate at first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:01:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they can be seen\Nthrough a single telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.82,0:01:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter compass of destiny\Nis leading your heart astray
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.16,0:01:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so turn the wheel in the other direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.06,0:01:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss aside your bonds and your past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can surely smile despite that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.38,0:01:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears shed trying to achieve\Nyour dreams aren't for naught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precious in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.21,0:02:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While God Eneru was busy dealing\Nwith Sanji's last-ditch efforts...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.56,0:02:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Usopp succeeded in rescuing Sanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.13,0:02:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Luffy's group...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...headed up Giant Jack to\Nsettle the score with God Eneru.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.91,0:02:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin! Eneru's after the gold bell, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.91,0:02:34.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Gyaaaaa!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.91,0:02:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's at the top of this vine, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.39,0:02:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They had but a mere\Nmoment to enjoy their reunion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.22,0:02:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for God Eneru, after repairing\Nthe Maxim, took action again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.20,0:02:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mamaragan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.71,0:03:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone! Hurry to the ship!\NI'll get Luffy and bring him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.28,0:03:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An exquisite view!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't assume things are gonna\Nturn out how you want, Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! He isn't holding back!\NWe gotta get outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that where the detestable\NShandoran warriors' hidden village is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're originally from the Blue Sea;\Nsurely they'd enjoy going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then! Strike the world below!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our village!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.47,0:04:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close! We'd be ashes\Nnow had we left any later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.51,0:04:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the name of Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...light the fire of Shandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.86,0:04:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wyper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.03,0:04:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your distant ancestor,\NGreat Warrior Calgara,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had another reason for being so\Ndetermined to take back our homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.61,0:04:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was Calgara's greatest regret of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Great Warrior Calgara\Nhad a very close friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.89,0:04:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A close friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He met Calgara 400\Nyears ago. His name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Montblanc Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.47,0:05:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Led by a Bell's Sound! Tale of\Nthe Great Warrior and the Explorer"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.02,0:05:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tale took place 400 years ago,\Nand though it has never been written of,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.32,0:05:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has been kept in people's hearts\Nfrom one generation to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.60,0:05:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a true story of a\Nwarrior known as a monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.50,0:05:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and an adventurer known as a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get on board, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.04,0:05:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster of Shandora is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Cast off! Cast off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.38,0:06:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--B-But there are still crewmen--!\N--Just get us out to sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.54,0:06:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.26,0:06:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave all your belongings and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Reporting, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our ship's stores have finally been exhausted,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:07:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,meaning we're now... lost... at sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cook's fainted!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.78,0:07:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! There's no food left!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commodore fell into the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.42,0:07:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Grand Line! Did he decide\Nto drown himself and leave us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was so starved he chose death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.56,0:07:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! He's a hero who's\Nreturned twice from these waters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what're these carefully\Nfolded clothes and shoes for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Someone go check...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.14,0:07:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that! It's a sea of monsters down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not coming back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Commodore!\N--Pretty nimble guy, he was. Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What's this rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this, Commodore?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.19,0:07:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell us you killed it underwater?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.26,0:07:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cook it up for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.63,0:07:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do lose your\Ntouch when you get lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.83,0:07:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a huge storm, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.84,0:08:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet so, given this swaying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.01,0:08:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet so? Is that all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.41,0:08:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The yardarm's been busted!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.18,0:08:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Where?!\N--Main! Main!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.15,0:08:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This third voyage has lasted over two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.75,0:08:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost miraculous it has lasted so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.99,0:08:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Did you just hear something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.19,0:08:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Do you mean the thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, something beautiful, like a bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest! Try to keep your senses!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This land is cursed! At this rate,\Nthe Shandians will be wiped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.04,0:08:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can we save the village, Priest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.88,0:08:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Offer... a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:08:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the sacrificial altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.36,0:08:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many victims does that make?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over a hundred...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.24,0:09:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?! This has\Nnever happened to us before!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.61,0:09:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can be of use, I will gladly give my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.02,0:09:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you cry, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.22,0:09:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to be welcomed by the sun god!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being chosen to be a sacrifice\Nis a wonderful thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for raising me, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.94,0:09:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.44,0:09:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is a bad dream, let me wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.65,0:09:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.49,0:09:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.16,0:10:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.49,0:10:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be like you someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.20,0:10:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be a brave warrior\Nand fight to protect this land!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.44,0:10:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna die because\Nof something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.41,0:10:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.45,0:10:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There really was an island in\Nthe direction you said to turn to!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.25,0:10:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what a relief. We can\Nride out the storm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.46,0:10:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, did you guys really not hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.73,0:10:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. None of us heard any bells. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.03,0:10:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You must've been\Nhearing things, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a magnificent forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we find good research materials!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.99,0:11:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! Was that the sound you heard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! Don't tease me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.53,0:11:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never mistake the sounds of\Nthis odd bird for something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.67,0:11:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Commodore! Was this--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.02,0:11:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... What a beautiful tone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.66,0:11:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems there are people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.20,0:11:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, Commodore! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.50,0:11:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's lying on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.04,0:11:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... Intruders!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.88,0:12:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey! Kid!\N--Commodore! This kid doesn't look right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.22,0:12:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Kinetsu plague.\NHe hasn't been treated at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.16,0:12:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This island is bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor! Do we have any Conine left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.00,0:12:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inject this lad and all of us immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.74,0:12:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad. Even the crops\Nare being eaten away at...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.18,0:12:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! All the houses\Nare filled with the sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.98,0:13:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the girl to the altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God of the sun... God of the rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God of the forest... God of the earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for this girl's life,\Nplease save our village!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.09,0:13:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Kashi God!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her go! It's for the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.37,0:14:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kashi God has such a divine form!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.34,0:14:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.71,0:14:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save my son and father!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the--?! Something fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.45,0:14:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.77,0:14:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth?! Who is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.01,0:14:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kashi God!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.31,0:14:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God-killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.18,0:14:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.52,0:14:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must've been really frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.09,0:14:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're safe now! There's no need to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.96,0:15:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Kashi God! Please forgive us!\N--We're all going to be cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill! Give more lives to the gods!\NBefore we incur their wrath!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Calgara! Kill him!\N--Sounds like he did something bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're really freaking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--He doesn't know how to ignore!\N--He killed a god? What's that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.28,0:15:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tribal rituals ain't something\Nyou mess around with!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.92,0:15:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quell the gods' anger,\NGreat Warrior Calgara-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.62,0:15:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am an explorer from\Nthe North Blue, Montblanc--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.22,0:15:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter who you are!\NYou must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this how you've eliminated all\Nthe few, yet vital advancements?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.20,0:15:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in no place to criticize!\NAtone to the gods where you stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that man?! He's holding\Nhis own against Calgara!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.48,0:16:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! Use that knife to take your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sacrifice meant to save the village,\Ncrying because she wants to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.33,0:16:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you no shame?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.07,0:16:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.25,0:16:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.39,0:16:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For centuries we've strictly\Nupheld the commandment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.96,0:16:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that all intruders on this\Nisland must be punished!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.07,0:16:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, you're a god-killer!\NYou, alone, won't be enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.07,0:16:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and all your men will pay with your lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lives" this, "sacrifices" that!\NWill those make your gods happy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These ceremonies are flat-out denials
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the triumphs of all the great men\Nbefore us! I won't stand for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an insult to all the\Nadventurers and researchers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.83,0:17:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who've ever set out to sea in the\Nhopes of bringing people happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.40,0:17:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your gods value people's lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.34,0:17:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then wouldn't they have contempt\Nfor these ceremonies, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.01,0:17:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.85,0:17:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll banish this so-called curse of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.48,0:17:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I can't, you can do whatever you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.12,0:17:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're a god or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In return, if I do save this village from tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.63,0:17:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,swear to me you'll never\Nhold these ceremonies again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.67,0:18:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you have to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.67,0:18:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such nonsense! Now you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.07,0:18:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.91,0:18:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.01,0:18:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These people have until\Ntomorrow evening to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.89,0:18:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.06,0:18:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's "goodbye, world" come sunset tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.13,0:18:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have faith in the commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, girlie. I feel bad for you too;\Nyou were born in this village...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.94,0:18:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! With your looks,\Nyou could marry an aristocrat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off, guys! Don't you have any tact?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.95,0:18:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.48,0:18:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean the commodore?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.98,0:18:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's Montblanc Noland,\Na renowned explorer. And a botanist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He visits uncharted islands and finds\Nand researches new plants there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.96,0:18:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's pretty much a hero back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's too good-natured...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.17,0:19:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And his biggest flaw is that\Nhe can't ignore stuff like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.37,0:19:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do trust him, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you let Calgara kill him there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer will make itself known tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.15,0:19:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he can save our village.\NThere is no harm in waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so carefree?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.35,0:19:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll listen to him, but not\Nthe priest's last words?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara! Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I sense the village is in\Neven the slightest danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.40,0:19:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take that man's head without\Nwaiting for tomorrow's sun to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.97,0:19:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not have the power\Nto hear the gods' voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do know when a man is\Nspeaking earnest words. That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.49,0:19:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should you really be up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all better...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.63,0:20:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does "advancement" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.78,0:20:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are! A Cona tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.35,0:20:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be surprised if there wasn't\None in such a big forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.85,0:20:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthquake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.59,0:20:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's happening! It's really happening!\N--It's the Kashi God's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.70,0:20:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.88,0:20:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... The forest floor has sunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.55,0:21:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the island is about to tear apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.26,0:21:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.36,0:21:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems the gods have given a\Ncrushing blow to you directly!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.40,0:21:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, these gods...\Naren't that great... at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.71,0:21:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even have the strength...\Nto kill a single person...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.22,0:21:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but could you get lost?\NI don't feel like looking at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.56,0:21:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... must hurry to the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.26,0:21:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amusing. I think I'll see this through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just try and squirm out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.17,0:21:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're feeling lonely, talk to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.68,0:22:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gaze at the heavens\Nas you wander about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.78,0:22:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the moon,\Nyou keep your gaze constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.66,0:22:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your deep reflection wanes\Nas you slowly disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.84,0:22:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay as you are, let those words guide you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.02,0:22:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream, you travelers who spend\Ncountless nights drifting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.10,0:22:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you may not be able to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.53,0:23:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will surely start moving forward again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.31,0:23:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How unsightly! Is this the wreck\Nof a man who defied the gods?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.89,0:23:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will your village die by curse, or by disease?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.49,0:23:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Are you that afraid of your gods?!\N--Don't talk like you understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.19,0:23:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However great your gods are,\Npeople's lives are even more precious!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.20,0:23:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.53,0:23:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Free from the Spell!\NThe Great Warrior Sheds Tears!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.73,0:23:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
